Musa Pam, Jos The Plateau State Executive Members of Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) has suspended its State Chairman Hon. Damishi Sango and Deputy Hon. Amos Gombi on Wednesday Morning in Jos for misappropriation Presidential campaign funds and divertion of N9.8 million internally Displaced Persons Funds. State Publicity Secretary of the Party in the State Hon. John Akans disclosed while in Press Conference at the Party Secretariat in Jos Akans said out of the 27 members of the State Executive of the Party in the State including three Vice chairmen, Legal adviser, State Organizing Secretary, Women Leader passed a vote of no confidence against Party Chairman and his deputy. “In a bid to save PDP in Plateau State the following resolutions has been reached, that the party chairman Hon. Damishi Sango and his deputy Hon. Amos Gombi stands suspended. “The money raised and saved by the party to help internally displaced persons (IDPs) to help relieve their pains were not accounted for up till this moment”. “That the resources sent to the state for the Presidential elections were not accounted for by the chairman aided by the deputy chairman concealed the amount sent by the Presidential campaign committee and created a fraudulent unseen template used as’ a sharing formula unknown to the state party structure and up till date no disclosure has been made by the chairman and the deputy “. However Acting chairman has been appointed by the State to take over the affairs PDP according to the State Executive members of the Party. “The Vice Chairman Northern Senatorial Zone, Hon. Chris Hassan shall take over the Leadership of the party as Acting State chairman” “That the state campaign Council is hereby dissolved with immediate effect, all party properties in whatsoever description is in their possession should be returned to the State party Secretariat within 48 hours”.